import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    data.plot(kind='line', x='year', y='pop', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['life_expect'], data['fertility'])
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='life_expect')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot()
    ax.bar(data['country'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which countries have the highest and lowest life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['fertility'].hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across countries?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='pop', by='cluster')
    plt.title('How does the population of countries in different clusters compare?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
